        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Remove the Stain Act</b></p> <p>This bill rescinds each Medal of Honor awarded for acts that occurred on December 29, 1890, at Wounded Knee Creek, Lakota Pine Ridge Indian Reservation, South Dakota.</p> <p>The bill requires the Army, Navy, Air Force, and Coast Guard to remove the names of those award recipients from the Medal of Honor Roll.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
